Package: preprocessr
Type: Package
Title: Functions to make your preprocessing life easier.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Karim Lahrichi
Maintainer: The package maintainer <klahrich@intact.net>
Description: The goal of this package is to provide a set of functions to make
    your preprocessing life easier. Most functions are intended to be used in the
    fit-transform paradigm (inspired from sklearn): you fit a preprocessing object
    to a training dataset, then used the object to transform a test dataset.
Imports:
    magrittr (>= 1.5),
    dplyr (>= 0.7.1),
    purrr (>= 0.2.2.2),
    R6 (>= 2.2.0),
    rlang (>= 0.1.1),
    Matrix (>= 1.2.7.1),
    GetoptLong (>= 0.1.6),
    lme4 (>= 1.1-14)
